          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:400; margin-top:2px;">
          How does Qatar play both sides of the Israel-Gaza conflict?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px; line-height:1.5;">
          Qatar plays a complex, dual role in the Israel-Hamas conflict. On one hand, it has helped mediate the release of Israeli hostages and facilitated the evacuation of wounded Palestinians and foreign nationals through the Rafah crossing. It remains one of the few countries with open communication channels with both Israel and Hamas, frequently acting as a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-17-may-25-tbq-h1-2-mediator?source=website" target="_blank">mediator</a> in ceasefire and hostage negotiations.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px; line-height:1.5;">
          Over the years, Qatar has provided more than $1 billion in aid to Gaza, including funding for fuel, electricity, and civil servant salaries, often in coordination with Israel. While Qatar insists this aid is purely humanitarian, critics argue it indirectly strengthens Hamasâ€™s grip on Gaza, as the group controls the territory.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px; line-height:1.5;">
         Qatar has also faced accusations of trying to influence Israeli public opinion by allegedly <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-17-may-25-tbq-h1-3-paying-off-israeli-figures?source=website" target="_blank">paying off Israeli figures</a>, including government officials. Its state-funded media outlet, Al Jazeera, is well known for amplifying regional narratives critical of Israel, drawing strong reactions from Israeli officials and international observers.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px; line-height:1.5;">
        Despite its public criticism of Israeli actions in Gaza, Qatar continues to hold quiet talks with Israeli officials behind the scenes. While it is praised for its mediation efforts, critics argue that Qatarâ€™s support for Hamas and tolerance of Israelâ€™s far-right politics undermine the chances for a lasting peace.</p>
         
        </mj-text>
